  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NGO Support / Wawas&apos; Democracy - pilot project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to contribute to the acknowledgement, acquisition and learning of civic values targeting children and adolescents of the educational establishments of school zone 4 in the canton of Otavalo, province of Imbabura. The project is based on proven educational methodology and work on human rights, citizenry and civic participation. The following activities are planned: Creating new interfaces between children, adolescents and important institutions in the community and increasing children&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;s and adolescent&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;s potential to civic participation through promoting awareness of the following civic values and skills: citizen participation, transparency, gender and social equality, inter-cultural values and environmental issues. Children and adolescents will also be encouraged to make improvement proposals and present them to the community and relevant institutions.</narrative>
  </description>
